- BBA-Agency
- Lottery

## Most Balanced Nuclei

Core, Governance, Dex, AxodusAPP, Marketplace, Academy, Mining, ACS, BBA-Agency and Lottery have D-levels that broadly match their current documented L-level and execution constraints.

## Most Documentation-Heavy Nuclei

Documentation, Business and Defi.

Documentation is documentation-heavy by purpose. Business is documentation-heavy by governance-support role while still having runtime/model implementation. Defi is documentation-heavy because execution-sensitive implementation remains gated.

## Most Product-Heavy Nuclei

Governance, AxodusAPP, Trading, Dex and Marketplace.

## Portfolio Recommendations

1. Keep D-level separate from L-level. Do not treat implementation depth as production authorization.
2. Use AxodusAPP as the next safe product sprint target because it can consume portfolio registries and status intelligence read-only.
3. Keep Business as non-executive coordination. Do not force Business into product execution merely because it is L4 Consolidated.
4. Keep Defi, Mining, Lottery, Trading, Marketplace and Dex execution-sensitive features blocked unless separate governance, treasury, compliance and validation approvals exist.
5. Add future D-level refreshes after each major product sprint.

## Suggested Next Product Sprint

AxodusAPP Integration Expansion.

Rationale:

- high implementation maturity;
- passing build/test evidence;
- central role as portfolio shell;
- can deliver visible value by consuming read-only global registries;
- avoids treasury, settlement, payout, wallet, DEX and trading execution.

